commentary: A piece has since broken off the fragment (cf. PAM 43269). This makes a reading of mem probable.

RECHECK: The character after a beth/kaf, how often does the scribe ligaturize these to join with the bottom of the beth/kaf. ROI#8 seems to be the trace of the middle horizontal branch of the Lamed, and thus connects with ROI#33. There are other occassions of the orthographical form of כל in Ktiv Cheser (cf. 4Q266 f 2 ii,5; f 5 i,18; f 6 iv,2)
